TensorFlow is an open-source software library for machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) developed by Google Brain team. It allows developers to build and train machine learning models, such as neural networks, for a variety of applications, including computer vision, natural language processing, and robotics.

TensorFlow provides a flexible and powerful framework for designing and implementing deep learning algorithms, with support for both CPU and GPU computation. It also offers tools for data preprocessing, visualization, and experiment tracking, making it popular among researchers and practitioners in the AI field.
